## Conventions

- Keep class damage output in line with the **DPR Benchmarks** by tier (see above).
- Use `---` to separate the Class Overview block from the Class Table and from major sections.
- Keep **Design Intent** and **Balance** blocks in blockquotes.
- In the Class Table, use `—` for empty cells and keep ASI and subclass feature levels consistent (4/8/12/16/19 and 3/6/11/17).
- Every level 5–20 that grants a base-class feature must have a matching subsection with at least one sentence of mechanics; do not leave "Scaling features (placeholders)" as the only text for those levels.
- Any class with Techniques, maneuvers, or similar named options must list each option with **name** and **effect** in a dedicated subsection.
- Reference existing docs in this folder (e.g. Monk Class Example, Class Overview) for tone and level of detail.
